fastqc: used for performing quality control on raw throughput seq data.
        * import BAM (Binary Alignment/Map)**compressed SAM(Sequence Alignment/Map)**human readable or FastQ files and lines start with '@'
        * provide overview to tell which ares may have problems
        * example comand : 
          module avail fastqc # is it downloaded
          module load fastqc # load it if its not
          fastqc <file>.fastq # run fastqc
          
Alignment to Reference: align sequence to a reference genome 
        * Tools: BWA
        * example command:
          module avail bwa 
          module load bwa
          bwa mem hg(37/38).fa <file>.fastqc > aln-pe.sam
          
Samtools: used to analize and manipualt files in SAM/DAM format
        * convert sam fle to BAM files:
            module avail samtools #check available versions
            module load samtools/1.13 #load specific version
        * sort BAM files
            samtools view aln-pe.sam -b | samtools sort > aln-pe.bam
            samtools index aln-pe.bam #
        * index BAM file:
            ls -lh aln-pe.sam
            ls -lh aln-pe.bam
Picard: Used to manipulate and modify SAM files
